		<div class="content-step-text">
			<h3>
				Viewings
			</h3>
			    <p>
			        After listing, you may be approached by potential buyers wanting to arrange viewings,
                    it is important that you try to keep an open schedule for this and make sure your house
                    is clean and well decorated for the viewings. You may want to reconsider certain styling
                    elements of your property, such as bright, bold colored wallpaper.
			    </p>
			    <p>
			        Certain styles may fit but may offput certain buyers. Whites, beiges and creams are
                    often safe colors to use when re-decorating for sale. Often, sales can proceed much
                    quicker and buyers can be enticed easier just by removing clutter and unnecessary
                    furniture from the home, making rooms feel bigger. Mirrors are also a great tool for
                    maximising space and making the most of smaller rooms.
			    </p>
		</div>

