			<h3>
				Legal
			</h3>
			    <p>
			        During the process of selling your property there are a number of legal hurdles you
                    should be aware of. When you list your property youâ€™ll need to provide an
                    <a href="https://www.gov.uk/buy-sell-your-home/energy-performance-certificates">
                        Energy Performance Certificate (EPC)</a>.
                </p>
			    <p>
			        We also have to deal with
                    <a href="http://hoa.org.uk/advice/guides-for-homeowners/i-am-selling/conveyancing-made-simple-for-sellers/">
                        Conveyancing</a>. Conveyancing is the legal
                    process of transferring the ownership of your property from you, to the buyer.
                    This is something you will need to have in mind when accepting bids from potential buyers and it is
                    generally good practice to arrange for the services
                    of a solicitor or conveyancer at the same time as listing the property.
			    </p>
